  + [focus_register] is first ready-for-inspection diversified corpus launch queue
  + [question_register] is whether to run corpus_boundary_delineation_010 through scratch-isolated validation
  + [delineation_register] is inside queue candidates, prompt packets, validation profiles, capture targets, launch commands, and queue outside
  + [periphery_register] is queue-not-proof, automatic launch outside, broad competence outside, project-root authority outside, and unrelated dirty files outside
  + [operation_register] is compile_prompt_packets, compile_launch_queue, extend_validator_cli, emit_tick_006, update_reentry_state
  + [evidence_register] is queue_001, prompt packets 010 through 012, custom validator support, and operating_loop_tick_006
  + [wisdom_register] is queue candidates should be inspected before launch and scored by family
  + [caution_register] is ready_for_inspection does not mean launched, validated, integrated, or competent
  + [balance_register] is stable because launch commands, validator profiles, capture targets, and outside are explicit
  + [integration_register] is pending commit, push, and optional first corpus candidate launch
  + [frame_outside] is hidden model state, broad local-worker readiness, worker file mutation, remote claims before push, and unrelated workspace changes

  = must: treat this frame as current visible attention state
  = must: return clock_state, proof_state, balance_state, drive_state, next_step, and outside to CurrentFocalPoint when this focus pass closes
  = should: open child frames only when a concrete benchmark, scoring, or worker-profile pass is needed

